76561198053422627,Recommended,528730,28880061,"Posted: 31 December, 2016",all,Zaxtor99 ® YouTube,"While this game is getting flooded with early negative reviews, I played it my first time expecting to play it maybe 20 to 30 minutes for an first impressions review.. and I ended up playing for about 1 hr and 45 minutes!Watch my livestream here (my scoring is at 1 Hour and 43 minutes into this video):https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zA0y31TsWI0Using my scoring system I use for all games, which is most heavily based on ""value"" and asking the question ""are you getting a good gaming value for your dollar?"".. this game scored an impressive 86% score from me.The game, while being pretty simple, offers very decent 3D graphics and nice textures and very fluid movement and controls.  Timing is critical, and while I already see some reviews knocking the game for being impossible to jump across lava to get the keys or not being able to hit enemies.. it's all timing and skill based movement to succeed.   Every enemy has a different attack style and speed and method and weapon needed to best defeat them.  If you aren't patient enough (or smart enough) to try different strategies or weapons, then this game might not be for you, but don't knock the game because of your lack of patience or logic.It's not a AAA game, but I think it's a very nice game for it's asking price, and it offers plenty of replay value as well with randomized dungeon layouts, multiple weapons to buy, and three levels of difficulty, as well as three attributes which can be increased with experience earned.One note: If you buy this game, PLEASE start on the ""easy"" difficuluty level which will allow you to save your experience and gold progession and advance through the game without getting too frustrated early on.Recommended to people who can appreciate a good old school type RPG game with simplistic controls and a game that will reward you if you go in not expecting a AAA game and if you are logical and patient.86% is my score."
