76561198115497313,Recommended,528730,28724608,"Posted: 27 December, 2016",all,Funhouse,"-If you want a retro dungeon game, this is it, 10/10.-Crypt of the Serpent King is a perfect example of a fun dungeon game! All for $2.99.You go through randomly generated dungeon levels to find all the keys to unlock the door to the dungon boss. The level styles are varied so it doesn't get boring and the levels are huge so your going to be looking at the mini map a lot if you get lost. If you beat the dungeon boss you get to move on to the next level and can upgrade your stats Strength, Agility, and Endurance with the XP you earned from killing enemies, you can also buy new melee and ranged weapons with the gold you found from loot.-It's a hard game that has 3 difficulty modes.-The music fits perfectly with the dungeon style of the game.-The graphics are simple and clean, but modern. It gives the game a nice retro look. The game runs at a solid 60FPS on ultra, and my PC isn't even that good. Really smooth gameplay."
